---
ai_image: true
title: Grilled Pesto Yogurt Chicken Thighs
source: Claude
tags: chicken, grilling, dinner
servings: 6
date added: 2026-04-14
---

In a large bowl, whisk together @plain yogurt{0.75%cup}, @basil pesto{3%tbsp}, @garlic cloves, minced{3}, juice of @lemon{1.5}, @olive oil{2%tbsp}, @kosher salt{1.5%tsp}, @black pepper{0.75%tsp}, and @smoked paprika{0.5%tsp} until smooth.

Add @bone-in, skin-on chicken thighs{10} and coat thoroughly, getting the marinade under the skin where you can. Cover and refrigerate for at least ~{1%hour}, or overnight for best results.

Pull the chicken from the fridge and let it come to room temperature. Set up the #grill{} for two-zone cooking — high direct heat on one side, medium indirect on the other. Oil the grates well. ~{10%minutes}

Place the thighs skin-side down over direct heat. Sear until the skin is charred and releases easily. ~{6%minutes} Flip and move to indirect heat. Close the lid and cook until internal temp hits 175°F. ~{18%minutes}

In the last couple minutes, place @lemon, halved{1} cut-side down over direct heat until charred. ~{2%minutes}

Rest the chicken for ~{5%minutes}, then squeeze the grilled lemon over the top and serve.
